                            },
                            {
                                "text": "Pension"
                            },
                            {
                                "text": "Termination conditions"
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "title": "Probation Period",
                "data": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "data": "The typical probation period is 3 months. If the person does not have an active pension fund, it can reach six months. Probationary periods are permitted by Israeli law, but an employee would still be considered a regular employee during such a period."
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
